From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] pinctrl: meson: handle PIN_CONFIG_INPUT_ENABLE and bare PIN_CONFIG_DRIVE_STRENGTH

Mainline meson_pinconf_set silently drops two parameters that the
Amlogic downstream pinctrl driver honours:

  - PIN_CONFIG_INPUT_ENABLE   (DT: input-enable;)
  - PIN_CONFIG_DRIVE_STRENGTH (DT: drive-strength = <N>;, N = 0..3,
    where the encoding maps directly to the SoC's 2-bit drive-strength
    register field - 500uA / 2.5mA / 3mA / 4mA on G12A)

Mainline only handles PIN_CONFIG_DRIVE_STRENGTH_UA (DT:
drive-strength-microamp = <X>;) and never handled the bare form, so
DTs ported from the downstream tree silently lose drive-strength
specs. PIN_CONFIG_INPUT_ENABLE has no handler at all.

Both are needed for the Spotify Car Thing's BCM20703A2 BT chip wake
pins, which expect:

    bt_wake_host: ... { input-enable; };
    host_wake_bt: ... { output-enable;
                        drive-strength = <1>; };

Add PIN_CONFIG_DRIVE_STRENGTH as a direct passthrough to the
pinctrl-meson DS register and PIN_CONFIG_INPUT_ENABLE as a wrapper
around meson_pinconf_set_output with !arg - the smallest change that
makes those DT properties reach the hardware.

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Upstream-Status: Pending
---
--- a/drivers/pinctrl/meson/pinctrl-meson.c
+++ b/drivers/pinctrl/meson/pinctrl-meson.c
@@ -358,7 +358,9 @@
 		param = pinconf_to_config_param(configs[i]);

 		switch (param) {
+		case PIN_CONFIG_DRIVE_STRENGTH:
 		case PIN_CONFIG_DRIVE_STRENGTH_UA:
+		case PIN_CONFIG_INPUT_ENABLE:
 		case PIN_CONFIG_OUTPUT_ENABLE:
 		case PIN_CONFIG_LEVEL:
 			arg = pinconf_to_config_argument(configs[i]);
@@ -378,9 +380,48 @@
 		case PIN_CONFIG_BIAS_PULL_DOWN:
 			ret = meson_pinconf_enable_bias(pc, pin, false);
 			break;
+		case PIN_CONFIG_DRIVE_STRENGTH:
+			/*
+			 * Bare drive-strength = <N> form (N=0..3 → register
+			 * bits 0..3 mapping directly to 500uA / 2.5mA / 3mA
+			 * / 4mA on G12A). Mainline only handled the
+			 * DRIVE_STRENGTH_UA form.
+			 */
+			if (!pc->reg_ds) {
+				ret = -ENOTSUPP;
+				break;
+			}
+			if (arg > 3) {
+				dev_warn_once(pc->dev,
+					      "pin %u: invalid drive-strength %u, expect 0..3\n",
+					      pin, arg);
+				arg = 3;
+			}
+			{
+				const struct meson_bank *bank;
+				unsigned int reg, bit;
+
+				ret = meson_get_bank(pc, pin, &bank);
+				if (ret)
+					break;
+				meson_calc_reg_and_bit(bank, pin,
+						       MESON_REG_DS, &reg, &bit);
+				ret = regmap_update_bits(pc->reg_ds, reg,
+							 0x3 << bit,
+							 (arg & 0x3) << bit);
+			}
+			break;
 		case PIN_CONFIG_DRIVE_STRENGTH_UA:
 			ret = meson_pinconf_set_drive_strength(pc, pin, arg);
 			break;
+		case PIN_CONFIG_INPUT_ENABLE:
+			/*
+			 * Stock pinconf-meson-common honours input-enable by
+			 * setting MESON_REG_DIR=input (bit=1). Mainline used
+			 * to silently drop it. Now mirrored.
+			 */
+			ret = meson_pinconf_set_output(pc, pin, !arg);
+			break;
 		case PIN_CONFIG_OUTPUT_ENABLE:
 			ret = meson_pinconf_set_output(pc, pin, arg);
 			break;
